{"id":14881596,"mediaExerciseId":"f7b7a835-a9fb-4b82-a4df-067927b5cd3f","exerciseName":"8","chapterName":"17","chapterTitle":"Dividends and Payout Policy","groupId":612428,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":601,"solutions":[{"id":5996776,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This exercise requires us to determine the reason why most companies chose not to pay cash dividends. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/3f58f8daca1b9aedd77dfac542871dec/125fe5403d78a5db2a5972e9d4ce2c96/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/3f58f8daca1b9aedd77dfac542871dec/125fe5403d78a5db2a5972e9d4ce2c96/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Dividend policy** is a company's policy used to structure  its payment of dividend to shareholder. It is determined by important factors such as the decision to pay dividends to shareholders and the decision to retain the profits to reinvest them in future projects.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/3f58f8daca1b9aedd77dfac542871dec/ea0a85eb7e1f80ec54ce609478dd3641/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/3f58f8daca1b9aedd77dfac542871dec/ea0a85eb7e1f80ec54ce609478dd3641/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"By distributing dividends or reserving dividends for future investment, most companies maximize the wealth of their shareholders. However, in some scenarios, it is not a simple decision to pay cash dividends. Most companies choose not to pay dividends because the